  card: {
    question: '<p>Why can using "©" for a copyright symbol be easier to code?</p>\n<p>???</p>\n',
    answers: [
      {
        text: "Because © isn't available on your keyboard.",
      },
      {
        text: 'Typing ©` on your keyboard is easier than using `&copy;.',
      },
      {
        text: 'There is no good way to code the copyright symbol.',
      },
      {
        text: '&copy; is smaller in filesize, loading faster.',
      },
    ],
    comment: '<p>Some characters are not easily typed on the keyboard, like the Copyright (©) character.</p>\n<p>To display the Copyright symbol, you can use either the HTML entity <em>number</em> or the entity <em>name</em>.</p>\n<p>HTML Entity Number: </p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x26;#169;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Result:</p>\n<p><img src="%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%22%20width%3D%22320%22%20height%3D%2254%22%3E%3Cg%20fill%3D%22none%22%20fill-rule%3D%22evenodd%22%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%22320%22%20height%3D%2254%22%20fill%3D%22%23FFF%22%20rx%3D%229%22%2F%3E%3Ctext%20fill%3D%22%23000%22%20font-family%3D%22ArialMT%2C%20Arial%22%20font-size%3D%2216%22%3E%3Ctspan%20x%3D%2220%22%20y%3D%2233%22%3E%C2%A9%3C%2Ftspan%3E%3C%2Ftext%3E%3C%2Fg%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E" alt="copyright"></p>\n<p>HTML Entity Name:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x26;copy;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Result:</p>\n<p><img src="%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%22%20width%3D%22320%22%20height%3D%2254%22%3E%3Cg%20fill%3D%22none%22%20fill-rule%3D%22evenodd%22%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%22320%22%20height%3D%2254%22%20fill%3D%22%23FFF%22%20rx%3D%229%22%2F%3E%3Ctext%20fill%3D%22%23000%22%20font-family%3D%22ArialMT%2C%20Arial%22%20font-size%3D%2216%22%3E%3Ctspan%20x%3D%2220%22%20y%3D%2233%22%3E%C2%A9%3C%2Ftspan%3E%3C%2Ftext%3E%3C%2Fg%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E" alt="copyright"></p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;p>Copyright &#x26;copy;&#x3C;/p>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Result:</p>\n<p><img src="%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%22%20width%3D%22320%22%20height%3D%2254%22%3E%3Cg%20fill%3D%22none%22%20fill-rule%3D%22evenodd%22%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%22320%22%20height%3D%2254%22%20fill%3D%22%23FFF%22%20rx%3D%229%22%2F%3E%3Ctext%20fill%3D%22%23000%22%20font-family%3D%22ArialMT%2C%20Arial%22%20font-size%3D%2216%22%3E%3Ctspan%20x%3D%2220%22%20y%3D%2233%22%3ECopyright%20%C2%A9%3C%2Ftspan%3E%3C%2Ftext%3E%3C%2Fg%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E" alt="copyright-year"></p>\n<!--[View CodePen](https://codepen.io/enkidevs/pen/WKRooB)-->\n<p>When using the Copyright symbol in your HTML, it is a best practice to use the corresponding HTML entity vs. cutting and pasting the symbol. Because  even if the symbol renders ok on your browser, it may not render the same on everyone\'s browser.</p>\n',
  },
}